    "build_provenance": "Replaces an absolute workstation interpreter path, which named a machine but identified no build. The M0.5 run predates automatic build capture (scripts/measure_parity.py now probes both fields at measure time), so these two values were recovered on 2026-07-20 from the interpreter that path still resolves to on the ratifying workstation - platform.python_version() and the tMAVEN distribution's PEP 610 direct_url.json - and the environment is not guaranteed unchanged since 2026-06-26. That tMAVEN checkout is an EARLIER upstream commit than the one the project pins for CI, installers and every live sidecar assertion (10f4230b6d13c6d2ad67b05d801696b4a40eff4a; see NOTICE, scripts/setup_sidecar.py, .github/workflows/sidecar.yml) - 13 upstream commits behind it, with tmaven/controllers/modeler/ changed in between. The interpreter differs too: the shipped sidecar stack pins python 3.12.* (sidecar/environment.yml), resolving to 3.12.13 in sidecar/conda-lock.yml. So this top-level tolerance was NOT measured on the build the live sidecar assertions run against; the ebhmm block under measured_by_method WAS. Mitigation: the measured worst cases here are 1.0 on both floors and 8.35e-09 / 1.00e-09 against ceilings of 0.02 / 0.01 (see pooled_worst), and the freeze only CONFIRMED the provisional PRD 11.2 defaults rather than widening them (tolerance == provisional), so no bound was derived from the older build's numbers. Re-measuring is a deliberate re-freeze and needs an ADR.",
